#. <section class="sutta" id="sn1.20"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn1.20:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 1"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 1"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn1.20:0.2"
msgid "2. Nandanavagga"
msgstr "2. The Garden of Delight"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn1.20:0.3"
msgid "20. Samiddhisutta"
msgstr "20. With Samiddhi"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "sn1.20:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
msgctxt "sn1.20:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati tapodārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha in the Hot Springs "
"Monastery."

msgctxt "sn1.20:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā samiddhi rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhāya yena tapodā "
"tenupasaṅkami gattāni parisiñcituṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Samiddhi rose at the crack of dawn and went to the hot "
"springs to bathe."

msgctxt "sn1.20:1.4"
msgid ""
"Tapode gattāni parisiñcitvā paccuttaritvā ekacīvaro aṭṭhāsi gattāni "
"pubbāpayamāno."
msgstr ""
"When he had bathed and emerged from the water he stood in one robe drying "
"himself."

# See BB’s note on gender here. While the comm, and the tenor of the text, suggest it is a female deity, Samiddhi uses avuso throughout, and I’m not sure that this can be used to a female.
msgctxt "sn1.20:1.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho aññatarā devatā abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ "
"tapodaṃ obhāsetvā yena āyasmā samiddhi tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā vehāsaṃ "
"ṭhitā āyasmantaṃ samiddhiṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then, late at night, a glorious deity, lighting up the entire hot springs, "
"went up to Samiddhi, and, standing in the air, addressed him in verse:"

# bunj here of course is punning between eat/enjoy; but in such cases I think it’s best to make the root meaning clear, otherwise the contrast doesn’t make sense.<a class="sc" id="sc2"></a><a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.19"></a>
#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
msgctxt "sn1.20:1.6"
msgid "“Abhutvā bhikkhasi bhikkhu,"
msgstr "“Mendicant, you seek alms before you eat;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:1.7"
msgid "na hi bhutvāna bhikkhasi;"
msgstr "you wouldn’t seek alms after eating."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:1.8"
msgid "Bhutvāna bhikkhu bhikkhassu,"
msgstr "But you should eat first, then seek alms:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:1.9"
msgid "mā taṃ kālo upaccagā”ti."
msgstr "don’t let the time pass you by.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.9"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:3.1"
msgid "“Kālaṃ vohaṃ na jānāmi,"
msgstr "“I truly don’t know the time;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:3.2"
msgid "channo kālo na dissati;"
msgstr "it’s hidden and cannot be seen."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:3.3"
msgid "Tasmā abhutvā bhikkhāmi,"
msgstr "That’s why I seek alms before eating:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:3.4"
msgid "mā maṃ kālo upaccagā”ti."
msgstr "don’t let the time pass me by!”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
#. VAR: pathaviyaṃ → paṭhaviyaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts2)
msgctxt "sn1.20:4.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sā devatā pathaviyaṃ patiṭṭhahitvā āyasmantaṃ samiddhiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then that deity landed on the ground and said to Samiddhi:"

msgctxt "sn1.20:4.2"
msgid ""
"“daharo tvaṃ, bhikkhu, pabbajito susu kāḷakeso, bhadrena yobbanena "
"samannāgato, paṭhamena vayasā, anikkīḷitāvī kāmesu."
msgstr ""
"“You’ve gone forth while young, mendicant. You’re black-haired, blessed with "
"youth, in the prime of life, and you’ve never flirted with sensual pleasures."

msgctxt "sn1.20:4.3"
msgid "Bhuñja, bhikkhu, mānusake kāme;"
msgstr "Enjoy human sensual pleasures!"

msgctxt "sn1.20:4.4"
msgid "mā sandiṭṭhikaṃ hitvā kālikaṃ anudhāvī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Don’t give up what you see in the present life to chase after what takes "
"time.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.20"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:5.1"
msgid "“Na khvāhaṃ, āvuso, sandiṭṭhikaṃ hitvā kālikaṃ anudhāvāmi."
msgstr "“I’m not, good sir;"

msgctxt "sn1.20:5.2"
msgid "Kālikañca khvāhaṃ, āvuso, hitvā sandiṭṭhikaṃ anudhāvāmi."
msgstr ""
"I’m giving up what takes time to chase after what I see in the present life."

msgctxt "sn1.20:5.3"
msgid "Kālikā hi, āvuso, kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā;"
msgstr ""
"For the Buddha has said that sensual pleasures take time, with much "
"suffering and distress, and they’re all the more full of drawbacks."

msgctxt "sn1.20:5.4"
msgid "ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn1.20:5.5"
msgid ""
"Sandiṭṭhiko ayaṃ dhammo akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo "
"viññūhī”ti."
msgstr ""
"But this teaching is realizable in this very life, immediately effective, "
"inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for "
"themselves.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:6.1"
msgid ""
"“Kathañca, bhikkhu, kālikā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, "
"ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo?"
msgstr ""
"“But in what way, mendicant, has the Buddha said that sensual pleasures take "
"time, with much suffering and distress, and they’re all the more full of "
"drawbacks?"

msgctxt "sn1.20:6.2"
msgid ""
"Kathaṃ sandiṭṭhiko ayaṃ dhammo akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ "
"veditabbo viññūhī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"And how is this teaching realizable in this very life, immediately "
"effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know "
"it for themselves?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:7.1"
msgid "“Ahaṃ kho, āvuso, navo acirapabbajito adhunāgato imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“I’m junior, good sir, recently gone forth, newly come to this teaching and "
"training."

#. VAR: Na tāhaṃ → na khvāhaṃ (bj, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn1.20:7.2"
msgid "Na tāhaṃ sakkomi vitthārena ācikkhituṃ."
msgstr "I’m not able to explain this in detail."

msgctxt "sn1.20:7.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho rājagahe viharati tapodārāme."
msgstr ""
"But the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha is staying "
"near Rājagaha in the Hot Springs Monastery."

msgctxt "sn1.20:7.4"
msgid "Taṃ bhagavantaṃ upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ puccha."
msgstr "You should go to him and ask about this matter."

msgctxt "sn1.20:7.5"
msgid "Yathā te bhagavā byākaroti tathā naṃ dhāreyyāsī”ti."
msgstr "And you should remember it in line with the Buddha’s answer.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.10"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.21"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:8.1"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, bhikkhu, sukaro so bhagavā amhehi upasaṅkamituṃ, aññāhi "
"mahesakkhāhi devatāhi parivuto."
msgstr ""
"“It’s not easy for us to approach the Buddha, as he is surrounded by other "
"illustrious deities."

msgctxt "sn1.20:8.2"
msgid ""
"Sace kho tvaṃ, bhikkhu, taṃ bhagavantaṃ upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ "
"puccheyyāsi, mayampi āgaccheyyāma dhammassavanāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"If you go to the Buddha and ask him about this matter, we’ll come along and "
"listen to the teaching.”"

msgctxt "sn1.20:8.3"
msgid ""
"“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā samiddhi tassā devatāya paṭissutvā yena bhagavā "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā samiddhi bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"“Yes, good sir,” Venerable Samiddhi replied. He went to the Buddha, bowed, "
"sat down to one side, and told him what had happened. Then he added:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:9.1"
msgid ""
"“Idhāhaṃ, bhante, rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhāya yena tapodā "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃ gattāni parisiñcituṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn1.20:9.2"
msgid ""
"Tapode gattāni parisiñcitvā paccuttaritvā ekacīvaro aṭṭhāsiṃ gattāni "
"pubbāpayamāno."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn1.20:9.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhante, aññatarā devatā abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇā "
"kevalakappaṃ tapodaṃ obhāsetvā yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā vehāsaṃ "
"ṭhitā imāya gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:10.1"
msgid "‘Abhutvā bhikkhasi bhikkhu,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:10.2"
msgid "na hi bhutvāna bhikkhasi;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:10.3"
msgid "Bhutvāna bhikkhu bhikkhassu,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:10.4"
msgid "mā taṃ kālo upaccagā’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:11.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, bhante, taṃ devataṃ gāthāya paccabhāsiṃ:"
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.22"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:12.1"
msgid "‘Kālaṃ vohaṃ na jānāmi,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:12.2"
msgid "channo kālo na dissati;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:12.3"
msgid "Tasmā abhutvā bhikkhāmi,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:12.4"
msgid "mā maṃ kālo upaccagā’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:13.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhante, sā devatā pathaviyaṃ patiṭṭhahitvā maṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn1.20:13.2"
msgid ""
"‘daharo tvaṃ, bhikkhu, pabbajito susu kāḷakeso, bhadrena yobbanena "
"samannāgato, paṭhamena vayasā, anikkīḷitāvī kāmesu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn1.20:13.3"
msgid "Bhuñja, bhikkhu, mānusake kāme;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn1.20:13.4"
msgid "mā sandiṭṭhikaṃ hitvā kālikaṃ anudhāvī’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:14.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vuttāhaṃ, bhante, taṃ devataṃ etadavocaṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn1.20:14.2"
msgid "‘na khvāhaṃ, āvuso, sandiṭṭhikaṃ hitvā kālikaṃ anudhāvāmi;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn1.20:14.3"
msgid "kālikañca khvāhaṃ, āvuso, hitvā sandiṭṭhikaṃ anudhāvāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn1.20:14.4"
msgid "Kālikā hi, āvuso, kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn1.20:14.5"
msgid "ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn1.20:14.6"
msgid ""
"Sandiṭṭhiko ayaṃ dhammo akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo "
"viññūhī’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.11"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:15.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhante, sā devatā maṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn1.20:15.2"
msgid "‘kathañca, bhikkhu, kālikā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn1.20:15.3"
msgid "ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn1.20:15.4"
msgid ""
"Kathaṃ sandiṭṭhiko ayaṃ dhammo akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ "
"veditabbo viññūhī’ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.23"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:16.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vuttāhaṃ, bhante, taṃ devataṃ etadavocaṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn1.20:16.2"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kho, āvuso, navo acirapabbajito adhunāgato imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ, na "
"tāhaṃ sakkomi vitthārena ācikkhituṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn1.20:16.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho rājagahe viharati tapodārāme."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn1.20:16.4"
msgid "Taṃ bhagavantaṃ upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ puccha."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn1.20:16.5"
msgid "Yathā te bhagavā byākaroti tathā naṃ dhāreyyāsī’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:17.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhante, sā devatā maṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn1.20:17.2"
msgid ""
"‘na kho, bhikkhu, sukaro so bhagavā amhehi upasaṅkamituṃ, aññāhi "
"mahesakkhāhi devatāhi parivuto."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn1.20:17.3"
msgid ""
"Sace kho tvaṃ, bhikkhu, taṃ bhagavantaṃ upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ "
"puccheyyāsi, mayampi āgaccheyyāma dhammassavanāyā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn1.20:17.4"
msgid ""
"Sace, bhante, tassā devatāya saccaṃ vacanaṃ, idheva sā devatā avidūre”ti."
msgstr "“Sir, if that deity spoke the truth, he’ll be close by.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:18.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, sā devatā āyasmantaṃ samiddhiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he had spoken, that deity said to Samiddhi:"

msgctxt "sn1.20:18.2"
msgid "“puccha, bhikkhu, puccha, bhikkhu, yamahaṃ anuppattā”ti."
msgstr "“Ask, mendicant, ask! For I have arrived.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:19.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā taṃ devataṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha addressed the deity in verse:"

# The obvious reading here is akkhati= express, as followed by comm and BB. However, there seems a tenuous connection with the previous passages. the Chinese parallels here don’t support “expressible”, although what they do say is unclear. SA 1078 has 愛想, perhaps from icchati, iṭṭhasañña? it also has 知所愛者 “one who desires the knowable ( jñeya)”. SA2.17 has 識於名色 “perceiving name and form”. I suspect that an original used a term related to akkhi/ikkhati which became confused. The Chinese terms don’t make this interpretation certain, but they are certainly closer than “the sayable”.
#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:20.1"
msgid "“Akkheyyasaññino sattā,"
msgstr "“Sentient beings who perceive the visible,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:20.2"
msgid "akkheyyasmiṃ patiṭṭhitā;"
msgstr "become established in the visible."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:20.3"
msgid "Akkheyyaṃ apariññāya,"
msgstr "Not understanding the visible,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:20.4"
msgid "yogamāyanti maccuno."
msgstr "they come under the yoke of Death."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.24"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:21.1"
msgid "Akkheyyañca pariññāya,"
msgstr "But having fully understood the visible,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:21.2"
msgid "Akkhātāraṃ na maññati;"
msgstr "they don’t identify as a seer,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:21.3"
msgid "Tañhi tassa na hotīti,"
msgstr "for they have nothing"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:21.4"
msgid "Yena naṃ vajjā na tassa atthi;"
msgstr "by which they might be described."

# Text takes these lines as verse, BB treats as prose; but they seem metrical to me.
#. <br>
#. VAR: yakkhā”ti → yakkhīti (pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn1.20:21.5"
msgid "Sace vijānāsi vadehi yakkhā”ti."
msgstr "Tell me if you understand, spirit.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:22.1"
msgid ""
"“Na khvāhaṃ, bhante, imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa vitthārena "
"atthaṃ ājānāmi."
msgstr ""
"“I don’t understand the detailed meaning of the Buddha’s brief statement."

msgctxt "sn1.20:22.2"
msgid ""
"Sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā tathā bhāsatu yathāhaṃ imassa bhagavatā "
"saṅkhittena bhāsitassa vitthārena atthaṃ jāneyyan”ti."
msgstr "Please teach me this matter so I can understand the detailed meaning.”"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.12"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.25"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
#. VAR: uda vā → athavā (si, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn1.20:23.1"
msgid "“Samo visesī uda vā nihīno,"
msgstr "“If you think that ‘I’m equal,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: vivadetha → sopi vadetha (mr)
msgctxt "sn1.20:23.2"
msgid "Yo maññatī so vivadetha tena;"
msgstr "special, or worse’, you’ll get into arguments."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:23.3"
msgid "Tīsu vidhāsu avikampamāno,"
msgstr "Unwavering in the face of the three discriminations,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:23.4"
msgid "Samo visesīti na tassa hoti;"
msgstr "you’ll have no thought ‘I’m equal or special’."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:23.5"
msgid "Sace vijānāsi vadehi yakkhā”ti."
msgstr "Tell me if you understand, spirit.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:24.1"
msgid ""
"“Imassapi khvāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa na vitthārena "
"atthaṃ ājānāmi."
msgstr ""
"“I don’t understand the detailed meaning of the Buddha’s brief statement."

msgctxt "sn1.20:24.2"
msgid ""
"Sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā tathā bhāsatu yathāhaṃ imassa bhagavatā "
"saṅkhittena bhāsitassa vitthārena atthaṃ jāneyyan”ti."
msgstr "Please teach me this matter so I can understand the detailed meaning.”"

# See BB for readings here.
#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:25.1"
msgid "“Pahāsi saṅkhaṃ na vimānamajjhagā,"
msgstr "“Reckoning’s given up, conceit rejected;"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Acchecchi → acchejji (si, s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn1.20:25.2"
msgid "Acchecchi taṇhaṃ idha nāmarūpe;"
msgstr "craving for name and form is cut off right here."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:25.3"
msgid "Taṃ chinnaganthaṃ anighaṃ nirāsaṃ,"
msgstr "They’ve cut the ties, untroubled and free of hope."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:25.4"
msgid "Pariyesamānā nājjhagamuṃ;"
msgstr "Though gods and humans search for them"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:25.5"
msgid "Devā manussā idha vā huraṃ vā,"
msgstr "in this world and the world beyond, they never find them,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:25.6"
msgid "Saggesu vā sabbanivesanesu."
msgstr "not in heaven nor in any abode."

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:26.1"
msgid "Sace vijānāsi vadehi yakkhā”ti."
msgstr "Tell me if you understand, spirit.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:27.1"
msgid ""
"“Imassa khvāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa evaṃ vitthārena "
"atthaṃ ājānāmi—"
msgstr ""
"“This is how I understand the detailed meaning of the Buddha’s brief "
"statement:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.26"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:28.1"
msgid "Pāpaṃ na kayirā vacasā manasā,"
msgstr "“You should never do anything bad"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:28.2"
msgid "Kāyena vā kiñcana sabbaloke;"
msgstr "by speech or mind or body in all the world."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:28.3"
msgid "Kāme pahāya satimā sampajāno,"
msgstr "Having given up sensual pleasures, mindful and aware,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:28.4"
msgid "Dukkhaṃ na sevetha anatthasaṃhitan”ti."
msgstr "you shouldn’t keep doing what’s painful and pointless.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn1.20:28.5"
msgid "Nandanavaggo dutiyo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.20:29.1"
msgid "Nandanā nandati ceva,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:29.2"
msgid "Natthiputtasamena ca;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:29.3"
msgid "Khattiyo saṇamāno ca,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:29.4"
msgid "Niddātandī ca dukkaraṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:29.5"
msgid "Hirī kuṭikā navamo,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.20:29.6"
msgid "Dasamo vutto samiddhināti."
msgstr ""
